<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343340>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8 Zancleopsis cabela. Polyps from A) Saudi Arabia and B, C) Maldives.D) Tentacle with terminal and sub-terminal capitula. E) Maldivian polyp with medusa buds.F) Large stenoteles (ls), medium-sized stenoteles (ms), small stenoteles (ss), and desmonemes (d). G) small stenoteles (ss) and microbasic euryteles (e). H, I) Female and male medusae, respectively. Details of J) manubrium with female gonads and K) tentacles. Scale bars:A-C, E) 0.2 mm; D) 50 Μm;F, G) 5 Μm; H-K) ~ 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8343340/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

